Package JourneyPlanner

Class Time

  • java.lang.Object
    • JourneyPlanner.Time
  • public class Time
extends java.lang.Object
    A Time in 24-hour format. Can also be using to represent an amount of time in hours and minutes.

    • Field Detail

      • hour

        public int hour

      • minute

        public int minute

      • MAX_TIME

        public static final Time MAX_TIME
        Represents "infinite" time. That is time.isBefore(MAX_TIME) and MAX_TIME.isAfter(time) is always true for any time object, time. Moreover, add(time, MAX_TIME) = add(MAX_TIME, MAX_TIME) = MAX_TIME and subtract(MAX_TIME, time) = MAX_TIME

      • MIN_TIME

        public static final Time MIN_TIME
        Represents zero time: 00:00

      • add

        public static Time add​(Time t1,
                       Time t2)
        Returns the time object which is the sum of the two given times. If either t1 or t2 are MAX_TIME, then this returns MAX_TIME
        Parameters:
        t1 - : first time to add
        t2 - : second time to add
        Returns:
        the time object which represent the time t1 + t2
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of the parameters are null

      • subtract

        public static Time subtract​(Time t1,
                            Time t2)
        Returns the time object that is t1 - t2. If t1 = MAX_TIME, then it returns MAX_TIME (infinity - constant = infinity).
        Parameters:
        t1 - : time object to subtract from
        t2 - : amount of time to subtract
        Returns:
        the time object that represents t1 - t2
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of the parameters are null
